{"title_page": "2015 NASCAR Whelen Southern Modified Tour", "text_new": "{{Motorsport season\n| series    = NASCAR Whelen Southern Modified Tour\n\n| year      = 2015\n| previous  = 2014\n| next      = 2016\n\n| previouslink = 2014 NASCAR Whelen Southern Modified Tour\n| nextlink     = 2016 NASCAR Whelen Southern Modified Tour\n\n| footer    =<center>[[Whelen Southern Modified Tour#Whelen Southern Modified Tour champions|Champions]]&nbsp;<nowiki>|</nowiki>&nbsp;[[List of Whelen Southern Modified Tour seasons|Seasons]]</center>\n}}\nThe '''2015 NASCAR Whelen Southern Modified Tour''' was the thirteenth season of the [[NASCAR]] [[Whelen Southern Modified Tour]] (WSMT). It began with the Spring Classic 150 at [[Caraway Speedway]] on March 15<ref name=\"SC150\">{{cite news|url=http://hometracks.nascar.com/nwsmt_rain_delay_caraway_031315|title=Whelen Southern Modified Opener Postponed|first=Tim|last=Southers|date=March 14, 2015|accessdate=March 14, 2015|work=NASCAR Home Tracks|publisher=NASCAR Media Group, LLC}}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and ended with the Charlotte 150 at [[Charlotte Motor Speedway]] on October 8.<ref name=\"Dates\">{{cite news|url=http://hometracks.nascar.com/nwmt_nwsmt_release_121714_Whelen_Modified_2015_Schedules_Announced|title=Whelen Modified 2015 Schedules Announced|first=Jason|last=Cunningham|date=December 17, 2014|accessdate=January 2, 2015|work=NASCAR Home Tracks|publisher=NASCAR Media Group, LLC|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150106214716/http://hometracks.nascar.com/nwmt_nwsmt_release_121714_Whelen_Modified_2015_Schedules_Announced|archive-date=January 6, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Andy Seuss]], who entered the season as the defending Drivers' Champion, won the championship, three points in front of George Brunnhoelzl III. Five races during the season were televised in the United States on [[NBCSN]] by a [[Broadcast delay|tape-delay]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://hometracks.nascar.com/release_020415_NASCAR_NBCSN_Reveal_Robust_Broadcast_Schedule|title=Robust NBCSN Broadcast Schedule Revealed|first=Jason|last=Cunningham|date=February 3, 2015|accessdate=February 5, 2015|work=NASCAR Home Tracks|publisher=NASCAR Media Group, LLC|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205023822/http://hometracks.nascar.com/release_020415_NASCAR_NBCSN_Reveal_Robust_Broadcast_Schedule|archive-date=February 5, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Drivers==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n!{{Tooltip|No.|Car number}}\n!Manufacturer\n!Car Owner\n!Race Driver\n!Crew Chief\n|-\n!rowspan=2| 1\n| [[Ford Motor Company|Ford]] <small>{{Tooltip|8|1\u20134, 7-10}}</small>\n|rowspan=2| Kim Myers\n|rowspan=2| [[Burt Myers]]\n|rowspan=2| Matt Cromer\n|-\n| [[Chevrolet]] <small>{{Tooltip|2|5\u20136}}</small>\n|-\n! 2\n| [[Chevrolet]]\n| Joe Bertuccio Sr.\n| J. R. Bertuccio<ref group=\"N\" name=\"Bristol\">At the Bush's Beans 150 at Bristol, some WMT and WSMT drivers had to change numbers to avoid clashing with the other Modified Tour championship. The WSMT driver who had to change his number was J. R. Bertuccio, who drove car number 21, instead of his regular car number 2.</ref> <small>{{Tooltip|7|1\u20137}}</small>\n| Joe Bertuccio Sr.\n|-\n! 4\n| [[Ford Motor Company|Ford]]\n| Gary Myers\n| Jason Myers\n| Mike Queen\n|-\n! 5\n| [[Ford Motor Company|Ford]]\n| Bob Ebersole\n| Kyle Ebersole\n| Bob Ebersole\n|-\n! 6\n| [[Chevrolet]]\n| Constance Partridge\n| [[Ryan Preece]] <small>{{Tooltip|3|1\u20132, 6}}</small>\n| Tommy Grasso\n|-\n! 8\n| [[Chevrolet]]\n| Bobby Baldwin\n| Dalton Baldwin <small>{{Tooltip|3|1\u20132, 10}}</small>\n| Bobby Baldwin\n|-\n! 10\n| [[Chevrolet]]\n| Howard Harvey\n| Luke Fleming <small>{{Tooltip|1|5}}</small>\n| Kenny Minter Jr.\n|-\n! 11\n| [[Chevrolet]]\n| Eddie Harvey\n| [[Andy Seuss]]\n| Eddie Harvey\n|-\n! 12\n| [[Chevrolet]]\n| Donna Norman\n| Mike Norman <small>{{Tooltip|6|1\u20133, 6, 8, 10}}</small>\n| Reggie Rug